## ğŸ”‹ WHAT A RUN-ON *IS*

A run-on is when you combine two or more **independent clauses** (aka complete sentences) without the right punctuation or conjunctions.

> I love her she makes me want to scream.

Thatâ€™s two sentences pretending to be one. It needs a fix:

* I love her. She makes me want to scream.
* I love her, and she makes me want to scream.
* I love herâ€”she makes me want to scream.

Each version creates a different vibe, but they all give the reader a place to breathe.

