 PARALLEL STRUCTURE**

You ever hear a sentence that just *feels wrong*? Not because of what it says, but how it stumbles out of the mouth like it tripped on its own shoelaces? Thatâ€™s parallel structure, baby. When you break it, the whole sentence limps. When you use it right? It *sings.*

