## ğŸ”— WHAT THIS CONNECTS TO

Weâ€™ve talked about sentence length and how to create rhythm. Weâ€™ve seen run-ons explode from too much chaos. Now we start looking inside the sentence. Parallel structure is about *balance*. It sets up patterns in how ideas are built and delivered. And when those patterns go sideways, so does clarity.

---

## ğŸ¶ WHAT PARALLEL STRUCTURE IS

Grammatically, it just means this:

> When you list or compare things, they should be built the same way.

Thatâ€™s it.

If you start with a verb, stick with verbs.
If you start with a noun, keep the nouns coming.

> WRONG: I like running, to swim, and biking.
>
> RIGHT: I like running, swimming, and biking.

You donâ€™t need a degree to hear the first one wobble. It sounds like a mixtape of three different voices. The second one flows like a song.

