### Prompt 2: Write a speech or rant with three perfectly parallel linesâ€”then let the fourth one fall apart on purpose.

### Prompt 3: Take a messy sentence from an old draft and rewrite it with parallel structure. Make it flow.


Parallel structure isnâ€™t about sounding smart. Itâ€™s about giving your ideas the rhythm they deserve. Get your verbs dancing. Get your nouns in line. Youâ€™re building ladders out of languageâ€”and when the rungs are even, people can climb.

